Reasoning: The paper discusses the licensing of data in the fields of artificial intelligence and machine learning, which are both subfields of computer science. Therefore, it is likely to belong to one of the CS sub-categories related to these fields. cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories as they directly relate to artificial intelligence and machine learning. cs.CY (cybersecurity) and cs.CR (cryptography and security) are also possible categories as the paper discusses the need for increased transparency and fairer markets for data. Finally, cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes a taxonomy for data licensing.
